						<div itemprop="articleBody">
		<p>World Ovarian Cancer Day is May 8th, 2014!</p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Last year’s World Ovarian Cancer Day, the first ever, was a huge success! This year we are reaching out to new supporters who will pledge to help spread the word about the day and make 2014 even more successful! &nbsp;Your pledge to Build One Voice for Every Woman will assist in sharing much needed information about ovarian cancer and its symptoms with women around the world.</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Some Background Information about Ovarian Cancer: </span><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Ovarian cancer has the lowest survival rate of all gynecologic cancers, and is characterized around the world by a lack of awareness of symptoms and late stage diagnosis. Ovarian cancer is diagnosed annually in nearly a quarter of a million women globally, and is responsible for 140,000 deaths each year. </span><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Statistics show that just 45% of women with ovarian cancer are likely to survive for five years compared to up to 89% of women with breast cancer. </span><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">On May 8th 2014, organizations from countries around the world will unite to educate their communities about ovarian cancer and its symptoms. For women living with the disease, and their families and friends, World Ovarian Cancer Day builds a sense of solidarity in the campaign to overcome the disease. For others, this day will bring information and build awareness of the symptoms and risk factors of ovarian cancer. </span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">As partners in our cause, we urge you to join the momentum building as May 8th approaches. &nbsp;A dedicated website has been established for World Ovarian Cancer Day, www.ovariancancerday.org. </span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">How can you get involved?</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Your participation could be as simple as registering your organization on the world site (<a href="http://ovariancancerday.org/get-involved/participant-registration-form/">http://ovariancancerday.org/get-involved/participant-registration-form/</a>) and then adding the World Ovarian Cancer Day logo to your website with a link to the world site.</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Other ideas include:</span></p>
<p>- Including information and the link in e-news blasts to your constituents or members</p>
<p>- Scrolling a banner for May 8 on your website</p>
<p>- Posting the symptoms list in your offices – check the website for posters and fact sheets</p>
<p>- Following World Ovarian Cancer Day on Facebook &lt;image006.png&gt;, Twitter &nbsp;&lt;image008.png&gt; and Pinterest &lt;image009.png&gt;</p>
<p>- Wearing teal (the international colour for ovarian cancer). &nbsp;If you do – take a picture and post it on our Facebook site &lt;image006.png&gt;</p>	</div>

	
